# UI classNames — flat `_CLASS` exports

All Tailwind class strings live in the feature's **`constants.ts`** as individual
top-level exports ending in **`_CLASS`**. View files import and apply them; they
do not define layout or styling strings inline.

## Applies to

- Colocated feature components: `src/app/**/components/<Name>/index.tsx`
- Route wrappers: `page.tsx`, group/route `layout.tsx`
- Shared components: `src/components/shared/` (flat files use a `<name>/constants.ts`
  subfolder, same pattern as `error-state/constants.ts`)

## Excluded

- **`src/components/ui/*`** — shadcn primitives; do not refactor for this rule.

## Conventions

**One feature per `constants.ts`.** The folder path is the namespace — do not
repeat the feature name on exports. One export per class string, ending in
`_CLASS`:

```ts
// AdminSidebar/constants.ts
export const ASIDE_CLASS =
  "border-border bg-background hidden h-dvh w-56 shrink-0 flex-col border-r md:flex";

export const NAV_LINK_CLASS =
  "flex items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium transition-colors";

export const NAV_LINK_ACTIVE_CLASS =
  "bg-muted text-foreground font-semibold";

export const NAV_LINK_INACTIVE_CLASS =
  "text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent hover:text-foreground";
```

```tsx
// index.tsx — cn() stays here; string literals do not
import { NAV_LINK_CLASS, NAV_LINK_ACTIVE_CLASS, NAV_LINK_INACTIVE_CLASS } from "./constants";

className={cn(
  NAV_LINK_CLASS,
  isActive ? NAV_LINK_ACTIVE_CLASS : NAV_LINK_INACTIVE_CLASS,
)}
```

## Rules

- **No nested class objects** — never `FEATURE_CLASSNAMES = { ... }`.
- **No inline Tailwind literals** in view files.
- **Semantic names** — `NAV_LINK_CLASS`, `HEADER_TITLE_CLASS`, not utility names.
- **Conditional styling** — separate exports per variant; keep `cn()` in the view.
- **Dynamic fragments** — runtime-only parts (e.g. `next/font` CSS variables) may
  merge in the view; static tokens still go in `_CLASS` exports.
- **Size variants** — flat per-size exports (`SM_CLASS`, `MD_CLASS`) in that
  component's `constants.ts`.

## Anti-patterns

| ❌ Avoid | ✅ Use |
|----------|--------|
| `className="flex flex-col gap-4"` | `className={CONTENT_CLASS}` |
| `FEATURE_CLASSNAMES.page` object access | `PAGE_CLASS` flat export |
| `ADMIN_SIDEBAR_ASIDE_CLASS` in colocated file | `ASIDE_CLASS` (folder is namespace) |
| Variant logic inside one template string | Separate `_ACTIVE_CLASS` / `_INACTIVE_CLASS` |

This rule guides agents; it does not lint or auto-fix existing files.
